<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>The Bachelor's Izzy Sharman-Firth was sent home during Wednesday night's episode, missing out on a spot in the finale.</p>

<p>And the 29-year-old HR adviser has now revealed the truth behind her most raunchy moment on the show: her bathtub Zoom date with Locky Gilbert.</p>

<p>She told The Courier Mail there was an interesting story behind the date - and also revealed she wasn't alone in the room at the time.</p>

<p>Truth be told: The Bachelor's Izzy Sharman-Firth has revealed the truth about her memorable bathtub date with Locky Gilbert, which took place during 'Love in Lockdown'</p>

<p>'I did have my togs on,' she said, responding to rumours she had been naked on camera.</p>

<p>'I just had my straps down so it looked like I didn't. I was like, "Oh, my boss is going to see it!"' she added. </p>

<p>Three's company! She told The Courier Mail that she was wearing a swimsuit, even though she looked naked, and also revealed she wasn't alone in the room at the time </p>

<p>Izzy also revealed she had just one female producer in the room with her.</p>

<p>'She would set up the camera and she was there making sure everything was okay,' she said.</p>

<p>Izzy went on to explain that she was convinced she would make it to the finale, after her connection with Locky grew during coronavirus lockdown.  </p>

<p>Bye! On Wednesday, thrill-seeker Locky sent Izzy home alongside intruder Bec Cvilikas (right) </p>

<p>'He said a lot of things that made me think he was thinking about a future together,' she said, before confirming she now has a boyfriend.</p>

<p>'You don't really know the connections he has with the other girls,' she added.  </p>

<p>On Wednesday, thrill-seeker Locky sent Izzy home alongside intruder Bec Cvilikas. </p>

<p>Hard choices: Before leaving, Locky told Izzy: 'You're so amazing. You bring out the best in me. I've had literally the best time'</p>

<p>Locky gave his final two roses to former friends-turned-rivals Irena Srbinovska and Bella Varelis.</p>

<p>After embracing Bec, it was an emotional Izzy's turn to say goodbye, tearing up as she hugged Locky before he walked her out.</p>

<p>Before leaving, he told her: 'You're so amazing. You bring out the best in me. I've had literally the best time.'</p>

<p>The chosen ones: Locky gave his final two roses to former friends-turned-rivals Irena Srbinovska (left) and Bella Varelis (right)</p>

<p>Izzy replied: 'You've also got some amazing girls back there. Good luck.'</p>

<p>In the car, Izzy tearfully told producers: 'I saw myself standing at the end of this whole experience with Locky. I was not expecting tonight to go the way it has. I guess it wasn't meant to be.</p>

<p>'Right now, I'm just feeling really heartbroken. But I wouldn't change anything,' she finished. </p>

<p>The Bachelor finale airs Thursday at 7.30pm on Channel 10</p>

